Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle at neck join, gradual curve. Rectangular stamp with dolphin around anchor as symbol. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Menestratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0385.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1042)
